  "body": "## Issue\n\nDevelopers should be able to save DB data in a directory of their choosing, and not have to default to the global `config/.db` if they don't want to. This used to work but seems to have broken. \n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. `truffle init`\n2. Uncomment the db enabling code and be sure to set db.enabled to true\n3. `truffle compile` && `truffle migrate`\n4. `truffle db serve` and search for all projects\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nThe project you have just migrated should appear in the search results.\n\nWhat you expected to happen.\n\n## Actual Results\n\nThe project does not appear. When the path for the db directory is removed and the steps above are otherwise followed, the project does appear.\n\n## Environment\n\n* Operating System: \n* Ethereum client:\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`):\n* node version (`node --version`):\n* npm version (`npm --version`): \n",
